{"word":"εὐωχία","slug":"εὐωχία","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὐωχία</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <a href='S:εὐωχέω'><el>εὐωχέω</el></a>\n<el>(εὐωχία, ἡ,) </el><p/><i>good cheer, feasting</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <el>λόγων εὐωχίαι</el> <i>feasts</i> of reason, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/>"}]}